# Using Thunder client
 ## how to access protected routes
 1. copy and paste the url http://127.0.0.1:5000
 2. in the 'Body' use the JSON format to put in the users info e.g {
  "username":"admin",
  "password":"admin123"
}
 3. login method= POST to get the access token

 4. after getting the access token copy and paste it into 'Headers'   have the header as  'Authorization' and value as 'Bearer <JWT Token> leave a space btn Bearer and JWT Token.

 5. change the method to 'GET' now you should be able to access the protected routes.
 ## how to perform CRUD operations
 1. GET Copy and paste the url http://127.0.0.1:5000/products
   - GET by id http://127.0.0.1:5000/products/1
 2. CREATE method=POST create an new product copy and paste the url http://127.0.0.1:5000/products
 - In the 'Body' paste all the details of the product using the json fomat e.g{
  "category": "laptop",
  "featured": false,
  "image_url": "https://www.saruk.co.ke/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fsaruk-web-images.s3.eu-north-1.amazonaws.com%2FLenovo-IdeaPad-1-14IAU7-Intel-Core-i5-12th-Gen-8GB-RAM-512GB-SSD-14-Inch-FHD-Display-1.jpg&w=640&q=75",
  "name": "Lenovo IdeaPad 3 15IAU7",
  "price": 379.99
}
 - press send.
 - resopose should say {
  "message": "Product created successfully!"
}
 3. UPDATE method = PUT replace an entire record copy and paste the url with the id number of the product you want to update  http://127.0.0.1:5000/products/2
    In the 'Body' paste all the details  using the JSON formart e.g {
  "category": "Kit",
  "featured": false,
  "id": 2,
  "image_url": "https://example.com/images/mug.jpg",
  "name": "Mug",
  "price": 10.5
} you can modify the values of the keys i.e category- key "kit"-value
- press send
- Response should say {"message":"product updated successfully!"}

4.Delete method Delete

Enter URL with a specific id http://127.0.0.1:5000/products/2

Click Send
